<p>These collars are kind of rare, but if you stay in Chardok long enough to make a few levels, you will eventually see one.  If you don't intend to spend a lot of time in Chardok, then just go ahead and buy one if you can find it for sale.  I don't think I have ever seen one for sale in East Commons. <br /> <br />I used to horde money and insist on getting stuff myself instead of buying it.  Now I am level 54 and with the exception of outrageously high-priced items, there is NOTHING I can spend my money on that is better than what I already have hehe.  I wish I had spent some of that money as I was levelling.  I would probably be a couple of levels higher if I had been going after XP instead of trying to find equipment upgrades on my own. <br /></p>
